main event: A group of 8-12 unidentified flying objects were observed by astronomers in Morehead, Kentucky on January 28, 1962.
interesting points: The objects were described as white and dull in color, flying in a group formation rather than a definite pattern.
The objects traversed about 45 degrees of the sky in around 3 seconds, indicating a high rate of speed.
One of the objects changed position from right to left during the observation.
The observer reported experiencing a sick feeling in their stomach and difficulty speaking after looking at the objects.
A local professor's analysis suggested the objects were possibly birds, but the witness was an experienced amateur astronomer who had seen other natural phenomena before.
sighted object: 8-12 white, dull objects in the sky
